They discovered that the functioning of the Sun is based on the same basic principles as other stars: the activity of all the stars in the solar system is determined by nothing other than their brightness and rotation.
Luminosity is used in conjunction with rotation to define a star's Rossby number, which is related to plasma flow.
The lower the Rossby number, the less active the star is with respect to magnetic reversals.
